Each Mapping has a universal unique system identifier or **UUID**, which takes the form of an immutable alphanumeric string, for example, `90052299-a1c4-4d79-ae00-830b5cc05597`. The UUID may be used in various configurations.

It can be retrieved from the **Mapping editor**:

- Find the Mapping you want to adjust and open its **Mapping editor**.

- In the top toolbar, click the **copy button** next to the Mapping name to automatically copy the UUID to your clipboard.
